President Donald J. Trump has announced his fourth wave of federal judicial nominees. The nominations include Allison H. Eid of Colorado for the United States Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit, Ralph R. Erickson of North Dakota for the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit, Michael P. Allen of Florida for the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims, Dabney L. Friedrich of Washington, D.C. for the United States District Court for the District of Columbia, Timothy J. Kelly of Washington, D.C. for the United States District Court for the District of Columbia, Trevor N. McFadden of Virginia for the United States District Court for the District of Columbia, Amanda L. Meredith of Virginia for the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims, Stephen S. Schwartz of Virginia for the United States Court of Federal Claims, Joseph L. Toth of Wisconsin for the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims, Stephanos Bibas of Pennsylvania for the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit, and Claria Horn Boom of Kentucky for the United States District Courts for the Eastern and Western Districts of Kentucky.